
[1]fusil

   FU'SIL, a, s as z. [L. fusilis, from fusus,fundo.]

   1. Capable of being melted or rendered fluid by heat.

   2. Running; flowing, as a liquid.

                    FU'SIL, n. s as z. [L. fusus, fundo.]

   1. A light musket or firelock.

   2. A bearing in heraldry of a rhomboidal figure, named from its shape,
   which resembles that of a spindle.
